From: Joshua-Eisenhart <40147598+Joshua-Eisenhart@users.noreply.github.com>
Date: Wed, 1 Jul 2026 17:31:10 -0700
Subject: [PATCH 1/3] feat(eval): cr_cross_engine_parity evaluator pack

First Codex-Ratchet sim evaluator pack over the core/eval substrate.
A CR sim runs externally (via the sim runner) and emits Julia + JAX
result JSONs; this pack consumes them as lev.sim_eval.provider_evidence
.v1 records on the sim.julia / sim.jax lanes (non_authoritative_input),
computes max_abs_diff over a declared shared observable, and a
deterministic gate-policy decides pass/block on tolerance. Sims measure;
the policy decides; no LLM in the gate path.

Load-bearing, not decorative: the sensor recursively rejects any
provider evidence carrying a verdict/gate_proof/effect_receipt field
(sims cannot mint truth), requires both engine lanes present as
non_authoritative_input, and blocks on missing lane / missing observable
/ malformed record / disagreement beyond tolerance. Three cases cover
pass (real fingerprint-floor julia+jax agree on quotient_class_count_
full=5, tol 0), adversarial false-green (one engine perturbed -> block),
and missing-lane (-> block).

Pack test 4/4; typecheck clean; full core/eval suite 144/145 (the 1
failure is the pre-existing s2 truth-vocabulary cutover test, unrelated
to this additive pack). Loader auto-discovers via *.eval.yaml. Manifest
mirrors intent_conservation conventions exactly.

